      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Ergosterol, a precursor of vitamin D, has <i>λ</i><sub>max</sub> = 282 nm and molar absorptivity <i>ϵ</i> = 11,900. What is the concentration of ergosterol in a solution whose absorbance <i>A</i> = 0.065 with a sample pathlength <i>l</i> = 1.00 cm?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ29WIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--eb949a64ac22db6119caae47f8a33b27326b4e63/OChem_14_EC_034.jpg\" alt=\"The wedge-dash structure of ergosterol that has the chemical formula C 28 H 44 O.\">",
